answer_pairs.first_answer:
To compute $58_9 - 18_9,$ we need to convert both numbers to decimal, perform subtraction, and then convert the result back to base $9.$ 

First, let's convert $58_9$ to decimal.

\begin{align*}
58_9 & = 5(9) + 8(1)\\
&=45+8\\
&=53_{10}.
\end{align*}

Next, let's convert $18_9$ to decimal.

\begin{align*}
18_9 & = 1(9)+8(1)\\
&=9+8\\
&=17_{10}.
\end{align*}

Now, subtract the two numbers in decimal:

$$53_{10} - 17_{10}=36.$$

We need to convert $36$ from base $10$ back to base $9$. 

First, divide by $9$: 
\begin{align*}
36/9&=4,
\end{align*}

Then, multiply the quotient by $9$ and subtract it from the dividend:
\begin{align*}
36-4(9)&=36-36\\
&=\boxed{0}.
\end{align*}

