To find the value of the expression, we first need to simplify it by applying the distributive property and combining like terms.

\begin{align*}
(3x-2)(4x+1)-(3x-2)4x+1
&=(12x^2 + 3x - 8x - 2)-(12x^2 + 10x^2 - 8x)+1\\
&= (12x^2 - 5x - 2) - (22x^2 - 16x) + 1\\
\text{ Distributive property: Multiply each term inside the parentheses with $(4x+1)$ }
&=(12x^2 - 5x - 2)(4x) + (-5x - 2) + (1)
\end{align*}

Now, distribute and combine like terms:

\begin{align*}
(3x-2)(4x+1)-(3x-2)4x+1
&=12x^3-20x^2-8x-8x-2+(-5x-2)+1\\
&=12x^3-25x^2-13x
\end{align*}

Now, we need to substitute $x = 4$ into the expression.

\begin{align*}
12x^3-25x^2-13x &= 12(4)^3 - 25(4)^2 - 13(4)\\
&=12(64)-25(16)-52\\
&=768-400-52\\
&=\boxed{-250}.
\end{align*}

Final Answer: The final answer is $\boxed{-250}$.

