To find the degree of the polynomial $p(x),$ we need to analyze the terms in the given expression.

Step 1: Factor out the common terms from each numerator and denominator:

\begin{align*}
p(x) &= \frac{(x - b)(x - c)}{(a - b)(a - c)} + \frac{(x - a)(x - c)}{(b - a)(b - c)} + \frac{(x - a)(x - b)}{(c - a)(c - b)}
\end{align*}

Step 2: Notice that each fraction can be rewritten as:

\begin{align*}
p(x) &= \frac{(x^2 - ax - bc)x}{(a-b)(a-c)} + \frac{(x^2 - (a+c)x + ac)x}{(b-a)(b-c)} + \frac{(x^2 - (a+b)x + ab)x}{(c-a)(c-b)}
\end{align*}

Step 3: Multiply out the numerators to simplify:

\begin{align*}
p(x) &= \frac{x^3 - ax^2 - bcx}{(a-b)(a-c)} + \frac{(b+c)x^2 - (a+c)x^2 + acx}{(b-a)(b-c)} + \frac{(-ab)x^2 - abx + abc x}{(c-a)(c-b)}
\end{align*}

Step 4: Combine like terms and notice that the coefficients of $x^3,$ $x^2$ in the numerator cancel out:

\begin{align*}
p(x) &= \frac{-abcx}{(a-b)(a-c)} + \frac{(b+c)x^2 - (a+c)x^2 + acx}{(b-a)(b-c)} + \frac{(-ab)x^2 - abx + abc x}{(c-a)(c-b)}
\end{align*}

Step 5: Expand and simplify the second term to separate $x$ terms:

\begin{align*}
p(x) &= \frac{-abcx}{(a-b)(a-c)} + \frac{x^2(b+c - a - c) - x(a+c) + acx}{(b-a)(b-c)}
\end{align*}

Step 6: Expand the numerator of the second term:

\begin{align*}
p(x) &= \frac{-abcx}{(a-b)(a-c)} + \frac{(bc - a - c)x^2 - (ac + x)c + acx^2}{(b-a)(b-c)}
\end{align*}

Step 7: Combine the terms with $x$ to simplify:

\begin{align*}
p(x) &= \frac{-abcx}{(a-b)(a-c)} + \frac{(bc - a - c)x^2 - cx^2 - x^2 + ax^2}{(b-a)(b-c)}
\end{align*}

Step 8: Combine like terms:

\begin{align*}
p(x) &= \frac{-abcx}{(a-b)(a-c)} + \frac{(bc - a - c)x^2 + (ax^2 - x^2) + ax^2}{(b-a)(b-c)}
\end{align*}

Step 9: Simplify the numerator further:

\begin{align*}
p(x) &= \frac{-abcx}{(a-b)(a-c)} + \frac{(bc - a - c)x^2 + (ax^2 - x^2) + ax^2}{(b-a)(b-c)}
\end{align*}

Step 10: Combine the terms with $x$:

\begin{align*}
p(x) &= \frac{-abcx}{(a-b)(a-c)} + \frac{(bc - a)x^2 + x^2 + ax^2}{(b-a)(b-c)}
\end{align*}

Step 11: Simplify the numerator further:

\begin{align*}
p(x) &= \frac{-abcx}{(a-b)(a-c)} + \frac{(bc - a)x^2 + x^2 + ax^2}{(b-a)(b-c)}
\end{align*}

Step 12: Factor out $x$ from the numerator of the second term:

\begin{align*}
p(x) &= \frac{-abcx}{(a-b)(a-c)} + \frac{x((bc - a)x + x^2 + ax)}{(b-a)(b-c)}
\end{align*}

Step 13: Combine like terms in the numerator of the second term:

\begin{align*}
p(x) &= \frac{-abcx}{(a-b)(a-c)} + \frac{x((bc - a)x + x^2 + ax)}{(b-a)(b-c)}
\end{align*}

Step 14: Factor out $x$ from the numerator of the second term:

\begin{align*}
p(x) &= \frac{-abcx}{(a-b)(a-c)} + \frac{x(bc - a)x + x^2(x + a)}{(b-a)(b-c)}
\end{align*}

Step 15: Expand and simplify the numerator further:

\begin{align*}
p(x) &= \frac{-abcx}{(a-b)(a-c)} + \frac{(bc - ax)x^2 + x^2(a + x)}{(b-a)(b-c)}
\end{align*}

Step 16: Simplify the expression for $p(x)$:

\begin{align*}
p(x) &= \frac{-abcx}{(a-b)(a-c)} + \frac{(bc - ax)x^2 + x^2(a + x)}{(b-a)(b-c)}
\end{align*}

Step 17: Multiply both sides by $(b-a)(b-c)$:

\begin{align*}
p(x) (b-a)(b-c) &= (-abcx)((b-a)(b-c)) + ((bc - ax)x^2 + x^2(a + x))
\end{align*}

Step 18: Expand the left side of the equation and simplify the right side:

\begin{align*}
p(x) (b-a)(b-c) &= (-abcx)(b-bc) + ((bc - ax)x^2 + x^2(a + x))\\
p(x) (b-a)(b-c) &= (-abcx)(b-bc) + (bx^2 - ax^3 + bx^2a + bx^3)
\end{align*}

Step 19: Combine like terms on the right side:

\begin{align*}
p(x) (b-a)(b-c) &= b(b-c)(-abcx) + x^2(b + c)x\\
p(x) (b-a)(b-c) &= -abcx(b-bc) + x^2(b + c)x
\end{align*}

Step 20: Factor out $bc$ from the terms with $bc$ in them:

\begin{align*}
p(x) (b-a)(b-c) &= b(bc)((-abcx)/b) + x^2((b + c)x)
\end{align*}

Step 21: Simplify and factor $x^3$ out of the terms with $bc$ in them:

\begin{align*}
p(x) (b-a)(b-c) &= bc(-axcx)(-abc) + x^2((b + c)x)
\end{align*}

Step 22: Simplify and factor $x^3$ out of the terms with $bc$ in them:

\begin{align*}
p(x) (b-a)(b-c) &= bc(-axcx)(-abc) + x^2((b + c)x)
\end{align*}

Step 23: Factor out $(b+c)$ from both terms on the right side and simplify further:

\begin{align*}
p(x) (b-a)(b-c) &= (x - b)(x - c)b(a - c) + x^2(b + c)
\end{align*}

Step 24: Factor out $(a-b)$ from both terms on the left side and simplify further:

\begin{align*}
p(x) (b-a)(b-c) &= -(bc)(-axcx)(x - b)(x - c) + x^2(b + c)
\end{align*}

Step 25: Factor out $x$ from both terms on the left side and simplify further:

\begin{align*}
p(x) (b-a)(b-c) &= x(bc)(-axcx)(-bc)(1 - b)(1 - c) + x^2(b + c)
\end{align*}

Step 26: Factor out $x$ from both terms on the left side and simplify further:

\begin{align*}
p(x) (b-a)(b-c) &= x(bc)x(-axcx)(-bc)(1 - b)(1 - c)
\end{align*}

Step 27: Simplify and factor out $(1-b)$ from both terms on the left side:

\begin{align*}
p(x) (b-a)(b-c) &= x(bc)x(-axcx)(-bc)(1 - b)(1 - c)\\
p(x) (b-a)(b-c) &= x(bc)x(-axcx)(-bc)
\end{align*}

Step 28: Factor out $x$ from both terms on the left side:

\begin{align*}
p(x) (b-a)(b-c) &= x^2x(bc)x(-axcx)(-bc)
\end{align*}

Step 29: Simplify and factor out $(1-b)$ from both terms on the right side:

\begin{align*}
p(x) (b-a)(b-c) &= -x^3x(bc)(bc)
\end{align*}

Step 30: Factor out $-1$ from the right side of the equation:

\begin{align*}
p(x) (b-a)(b-c) = x^2x(-axcx)(1-b)(bc)
\end{align*}

Step 31: Simplify and factor out $(1-b)$ from both terms on the left side:

\begin{align*}
p(x) (b-a)(b-c) &= x^2x(-axcx)(1 - b)(bc)\\
p(x) (b-a)(b-c) &= x^3x(-axcx)
\end{align*}

Step 32: Factor out $x$ from both terms on the left side:

\begin{align*}
p(x) (b-a)(b-c) &= x^4(-axcx)
\end{align*}

The final answer is: $\boxed{x^3(-axcx)}$

